## Operator Breakdown

- **σ (Air/Aerunik — Distinction)**: visible|invisible — Pretas occupy spaces perceptible only through heightened awareness or yogic practice.
- **ρ (Water/Sentaria — Relation)**: attachment|longing — Perpetual desire defines the preta condition; craving is never satisfied.
- **λ (Fire/Jvalion — Transformation)**: ignorance|insight — Recognizing pretas as mind-dependent reveals the nature of suffering itself.
- **β (Wood/Arboriel — Growth)**: suffering|liberation — Pretas serve as both literal beings and metaphors for the human condition of attachment.
- **δγ (Earth/Humavita — Cycling)**: realm|realm — Overlapping realms interpenetrate with ordinary experience.
- **μ (Metal/Ferrosid — Structure)**: perception|reality — The mind-dependent nature of pretas reflects Buddhist insights about phenomenal existence.

## Z-State
